<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="iddcf8593a-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06" identifier="/us/usc/t12/s2904"><num value="2904">§ 2904.</num><heading> Report to Congress</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Each appropriate Federal financial supervisory agency shall include in its annual report to the Congress a section outlining the actions it has taken to carry out its responsibilities under this chapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="iddcf8593b-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06">(<ref href="/us/pl/95/128/tVIII/s805">Pub. L. 95–128, title VIII, § 805</ref>, <date date="1977-10-12">Oct. 12, 1977</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/91/1148">91 Stat. 1148</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
